        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:03PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Amherst, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amherst...
Bent Creek...
Clifford...
Riverville...
New Glasgow...
Tower Hill...
and Allens Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.

Additional statements will be issued as conditions warrant.</instruction>
